\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. capnoides} (L.) Pers.,{\i  Syn. Pl.}{\b  2}: 270 (1806) ({\i C. gebleri} Ledeb.; incl.{\i  C. alba} Mansfeld). Robust, ascending or erect annual or biennial up to 40 cm. Leaves 2-ternate, all petiolate; ultimate segments 3-fid or variously dissected. Racemes 5- to 8-flowered, lax. Lower bracts compound, like the upper leaves; upper bracts entire. Corolla 11-16 mm, cream or white, yellow at apex; spur 5-7 mm, slender; style persistent, straight. Fruit 20-30 mm, slender. 2n = 16.{\i  E. Alps }({\i local}) ;{\i  Carpathians; N.E. Russia.} Au Cz *It Po Rm Rs(N, ?C) [Fe].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. nobilis} (L.) Pers., {\i Syn. Pl.}{\b  2}: 269 (1806). Robust, rhizomatous perennial 30-50 cm. Leaves 2- or 3-pinnate, glaucous. Racemes 20- to 30-flowered, capitate. Bracts cuneate, dissected, much longer than pedicels. Lower pedicels 5-15 mm. Corolla c. 20 mm, yellow or white; spur c. 7 mm. Fruit 10-20 mm. Seeds black, shiny. 2n = 16.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized in Finland and Sweden.} [Fe Su.] ({\i C. Asia.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 (B) Perennials with tuberous stock. Stems simple, or with 1 or 2 branches, with 1-3 leaves on each stem or branch. Racemes terminal.
\par

