\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. C. uniflora} (Sieber) Nyman,{\i  Syll.} 185 (1855) ({\i C. rutifolia }(Sm.) DC. subsp. {\i uniflora} (Sieber) Cullen & P.H. Davis).Stem 5-15 cm, erect, without a scale below leaves; tuber solid. Leaves opposite, usually 2-ternate, glaucous. Raceme 1- to 3-flowered. Bracts broadly ovate, entire. Corolla 20-25 mm, whitish to pale pink, veined with purple; spur 10-13 mm. {\i Stony places above} 1500{\i  m. • Kriti.} Cr.
